author: Nikki Schwab
title: Economists fear doctored data from Trump administration | Daily Mail Online
text: show ad Economic experts fear that Trump's 'alternative facts' will spread to the doctoring of government data Economists have voiced concerns that Trump's administration - which bashes 'fake news' and has championed 'alternative facts' - will doctor government data Experts point to Donald Trump and Steve Mnuchin's claims that unemployment data is skewed - with far more Americans without jobs than the BLS reports There are fears that Trump's people could stimulate economic data to make the president look better or defund agencies responsible for research over all
